solution: We have $i^5 = i^4\cdot i = 1\cdot (i) = i$.  We also have $i^{-25} = 1/i^{25} = 1/(i^{24}\cdot i) = 1/[1\cdot (i)] = 1/i = \frac1{i}\cdot\frac{i}{i} = i/(-1) = -i$ and $i^{45} = (i^{44})\cdot i= 1\cdot i =i$, and . So, adding these three results gives $i^5 + i^{-25} + i^{45} = i+-i+i = \boxed{i}$.
model_output:
Remember that $i = \sqrt{-1}$.

We know that $i^1 = i$, $i^2 = -1$, $i^3 = -i$, and $i^4 = 1$.

Since $i^4 = 1$, we can reduce any higher power of $i$ when divided by 4:

$i^5 = i^4 \cdot i = 1 \cdot i = i$

$i^{-25} = \dfrac{1}{i^{25}} = \dfrac{1}{i^{4 \cdot 6 + 1}} = \dfrac{1}{i} = -i$

$i^{45} = i^{4 \cdot 11 + 1} = i$

Therefore, we have $i^5 + i^{-25} + i^{45} = i + (-i) + i = \boxed{1}$.
